description: Tragedy struck Amritsar as at least 14 people died and several others were hospitalized after consuming spurious liquor in villages under the Majitha block. Raids are underway to apprehend more manufacturers, with officials providing assistance to affected families and working to prevent further casualties.
title: At least 14 dead after consuming spurious liquor in Amritsar

author: TNN
description: Indian intelligence agencies have discovered a Pakistan-linked cyber-attack campaign, distributing malware named 'Dance of the Hillary' through social media platforms like WhatsApp and Facebook. This malware, spread via video or document files, steals sensitive user data and enables remote device control. Punjab Police issued a cyber alert, urging vigilance against suspicious links to protect personal and national security.
title: 'Dance of the Hillary': Guard your data, cops warn of Pak virus onslaught

author: PRATYUSH RAJ
description: In an exclusive interview with Timesofindia.com, former South Africa cricketer Mark Boucher goes down memory lane and recollects the time he shared the dressing room with a young Virat Kohli during his three-year stint with the Royal Challengers Bengaluru (RCB) from 2008-10. The former gloveman revealed how he helped Kohli hone his technique against short-pitched bowling and explained why his eagerness to learn and aggressive mindset laid the foundation for his stellar career.
title: Exclusive: 'There's only one Tendulkar and there's only one Kohli'

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Stock market today: Nifty50 and BSE Sensex, the Indian equity benchmark indices, tanked in opening trade on Tuesday a day after an over 3.5% rally. While Nifty50 went below 24,800, BSE Sensex was below 82,000.
title: Nifty50 flat tanks below 24,800; BSE Sensex dips over 500 points

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Stock market recommendations: Mirae Asset Sharekhan's Somil Mehta recommends buying CDSL and Indian Bank. CDSL, with a buy range of Rs 1290-1270, targets Rs 1378, having broken a downward trend. Indian Bank, buy range Rs 570-580, aims for Rs 615, supported by its 40-day moving average.
title: Top stocks to buy today: Stock market recommendations for today

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: In a controversial move, the Trump administration granted refugee status to 49 white South Africans, mostly Afrikaners, citing racial persecution. Welcomed by US officials, President Trump defended the decision, alleging a "genocide" against white farmers, a claim South Africa vehemently denies. Critics highlight the contradiction with Trump's restrictive immigration policies, while allies like Elon Musk support his concerns.
title: Trump cites 'racial discrimination' as first batch of white SA refugees land in US

author: AMIT KUMAR
description: Atul Wassan recalls a young Virat Kohli's early days, recognizing his special talent at age 12. Wassan nurtured Kohli, selecting him for Ranji Trophy. Kohli's impact on cricket is undeniable, similar to legends like Hayden and Gilchrist. After retiring from Test cricket, Kohli aims to enjoy life, focusing on IPL and potentially the Olympics, prioritizing family and personal fulfillment.
title: 'Virat ko chhod do, dusre bhai ko padha likha lo': The making of Kohli

author: etimes.in
description: Karnataka's beloved comedian, Rakesh Poojary, tragically passed away at 33 due to a heart attack on May 11. He collapsed at a friend's mehendi event and was immediately hospitalized. Known for his work on 'Comedy Khiladigalu,' where he was a runner-up in 2018 and winner in 2020, Rakesh also starred in films like 'Pailwaan' and several Tulu movies.
title: Who was Rakesh Poojary? Comedian who passed away at age of 34

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: Palantir has surged into the top 10 US tech firms, surpassing Salesforce with a $281 billion valuation after an 8% stock jump. Fueled by a 45% surge in government business, including a significant U.S. Army contract, Palantir's stock has quintupled in the past year. Despite Nasdaq's decline, Palantir's valuation comes at a premium, exceeding typical large-cap tech multiples.
title: America’s 10 tech cos have a new entrant that has 'beaten' IBM and Cisco

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Brokerage firms have varying outlooks on Indian companies. JP Morgan is underweight on Dr. Reddy's due to margin concerns, while Citigroup maintains a buy rating on Biocon despite weak numbers. Nomura is positive on Zydus Life following a key approval. Macquarie is underperforming on Swiggy, and Goldman Sachs has a buy rating on Pidilite, citing strong volume growth.
title: JP Morgan, Goldman Sachs & more: Top stocks on brokers' radar for today

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: The Indian Premier League is set to resume on May 17. Cricket Australia is backing players who opt out due to safety concerns. The World Test Championship final is approaching soon. Several key Australian players are involved. Coaches and commentators are also considering their return. The IPL's resumption will be closely monitored for both cricket and player safety.
title: CA gives major update on players unwilling to return to India for IPL

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Rajkumar Sharma, Virat Kohli's childhood coach, lauded Kohli's remarkable Test career following his unexpected retirement. Sharma expressed pride in Kohli's contributions and voiced optimism for his continued commitment to ODI cricket. He hopes Kohli will lead India to victory in the 2027 ICC ODI World Cup, anticipating another glorious chapter in his career.
title: 'He'll be there to ... ': Kohli's childhood coach's 2027 ODI WC prediction

title: Islamabad's nuclear blackmail won’t work: PM Modi

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Donald Trump's executive order aims to drastically cut US prescription drug prices, aligning them with the lowest prices in developed nations. Pharmaceutical companies face a 30-day window to voluntarily comply or face potential regulatory actions. The order targets intermediaries and promotes drug importation from countries like Canada.
title: 'Lowest price in the world’: How Trump plans to cut drug costs by 80%

author: RAJ SHEKHAR JHA
title: Pakistan’s ‘innocent preacher’ is actually a global terrorist

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Ajay Devgn's Raid 2 has achieved remarkable success at the Indian box office, accumulating over Rs 125 crore within 12 days. Despite a slight dip on its second Monday, the film benefited from the Buddha Purnima holiday and maintained a steady performance. The film's worldwide gross is approaching Rs 170 crore, with strong contributions from international markets.
title: Raid 2 box office Day 12: Ajay Devgn starrer hits Rs 125 crore mark

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Two Indian students from Cleveland State University tragically died in a car crash on the Pennsylvania Turnpike in Lancaster County. Saurav Prabhakar, 23, and Manav Patel, 20, were pronounced dead at the scene due to multiple traumatic injuries after their vehicle left the roadway and struck a tree and bridge.
title: Two Indian students killed in fatal road accident in Pennsylvania

title: US aims to slash drug prices, India shielded

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Ravichandran Ashwin reflected on Virat Kohli and Rohit Sharma's Test retirements, acknowledging the inevitable end to even legendary careers. He highlighted Kohli's unmatched energy and Rohit's potential, suggesting Rohit could have mirrored Kohli's achievements if not for an early injury. Ashwin also noted his own mixed performances leading to his retirement.
title: 'What Virat achieved, Rohit could've done too': R Ashwin

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Air India and Indigo have announced the cancellation of flight operations to and from several locations, including Jammu, Leh, Jodhpur, Amritsar, and Chandigarh, for today, May 13th. This decision was made in light of recent developments and with passenger safety as the top priority. Air India is closely monitoring the situation and will provide updates as they become available.
title: Air India cancels flight operations at 8 locations for May 13, issues advisory

description: Following a US-China trade agreement where tariffs are suspended for 90 days, President Trump claimed Apple CEO Tim Cook plans to increase US investments, potentially building more plants. This news follows reports of Apple considering iPhone price hikes, possibly linked to tariffs.
title: US-China trade: Trump says he called Apple CEO after China tariff rollback and ...

author: SWATI BHARADWAJ
description: Following Operation Sindoor, the Indian government is expediting missile production. Manufacturers in Hyderabad are working to quickly deliver critical systems for missiles like BrahMos and Akash. The Defence Ministry is also engaging with drone and anti-drone tech companies to enhance capabilities. Commanders have procurement rights to address vulnerabilities, especially aerial threats.
title: Border tension spurs Hyderabad missile firms to fast-track supplies

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Virat Kohli's recent Test retirement shocked the cricketing world, including his former coach Sarandeep Singh, who revealed Kohli was actively preparing for the upcoming England series and showed no prior indications of stepping down. Singh mentioned Kohli's eagerness to replicate his 2018 success in England, making his sudden exit unexpected, especially with the crucial Test series against England approaching.
title: Kohli's Ranji coach drops bombshell: 'He was preparing for England Tests'

author: TNN
title: Punjab moves HC for review of Bhakra water-release order

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Virat Kohli's sudden Test retirement has sparked a frenzy of reactions online, with fans sharing tributes and speculations about his ODI future. Having already retired from T20s, it's widely assumed the 2027 Cricket World Cup could be his last appearance. His coach, Rajkumar Sharma, lauded Kohli's Test career and hopes for ODI success.
title: Virat Kohli memes break internet as fans speculate on his ODI retirement

author: TOI TRENDING DESK
description: A recent MIT study in mice reveals dopamine's crucial role in fear extinction. Researchers discovered that dopamine activates specific neurons in the amygdala, linked to reward, which drives the unlearning of fear. This suggests that overcoming fear isn't just suppression but a positive learning process, potentially opening new avenues for treating anxiety and PTSD.
title: Fear can be unlearned—and this hormone can be the key

title: AIIMS Bhopal student in city for cultural fest found dead in AFMC hostel’s washroom

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Dwyane Wade celebrated Gabrielle Union on Mother's Day with heartfelt Instagram posts, showcasing their love and family bond. Union, deeply touched, reposted the messages with emotional emojis. Amidst Wade's health recovery and raising their daughter, Union also shared her experiences with racism in Hollywood, highlighting the challenges she faced regarding beauty standards and opportunities.
title: 'Our favourite you': Dwyane Wade pens heartfelt words for Gabrielle Union

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: US-based edtech firm Chegg is set to lay off 22% of its workforce, impacting around 248 employees, citing increased student reliance on AI tools like ChatGPT and Google's AI Overviews. Chegg also plans to close its US and Canada offices, aiming for substantial cost savings through restructuring.
title: US edtech company ‘blames’ Google, OpenAI for cutting 22% of jobs
